00:00:07.290 --> 00:00:10.700
we're going to be discussing in this lesson. The major

00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:14.530
pieces are you, your computer running a Web

00:00:14.530 --> 00:00:19.190
browser, the Internet, and servers. Your browser makes requests

00:00:19.190 --> 00:00:22.270
via the Internet to servers. These requests are

00:00:22.270 --> 00:00:26.520
using a protocol called http and the servers respond

00:00:26.520 --> 00:00:32.310
with files that your browser displays. Some examples of browsers are

00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:36.900
Internet Explorer, Chrome, Firefox. You're probably running one of

00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:41.560
